but because i don't focus on the enjoy & happiness of the actual PROCESS
it's always about the end results and the feedback
summary: so I don’t usually make posts about let’s players or anything (I mean... I surprisingly don’t even post much about games, wow)...
body:
so I don’t usually make posts about let’s players or anything (I mean… I surprisingly don’t even post much about games, wow) but I was watching jacksepticeye’s playthrough of “When the Darkness Comes.” I mean, I have depression and anxiety, but, despite the warnings, I knew I could handle it (and I did). But anyway, there was a pretty clear theme of just that: mental illness and how someone, especially a creator, copes with it. It also touched on social anxiety (scariest part for me because, yeah, I deal with that a  l o t ).

ANYWAY, what I’m getting to is actually a part where the player was asked “What is your purpose in life?” with the possible answers being “creation,” “fame,” “money,” “happiness,” and “knowledge.”

So, of course, I instinctively was like “oh, yeah, creation!” Didn’t think twice, though I did feel like money, knowledge, and fame (on some level) were up there. Didn’t even consider happiness.

And then Jack says that his is happiness and it absolutely blew my fucking mind. And he made a point: what are the others worth if you’re still unhappy? Plus, if you don’t have the others, but you’re happy, what does it matter, then?

Like, I’ve been on this earth almost 22 years and I never once considered that maybe my focus should be on happiness, even if that happiness comes from the creative process or something keyed into those other options. Like, maybe, instead of feeling the pressure of some grand, extreme purpose and hoping happiness will come with progress… maybe I just deserve to pursue happiness itself.

Q podriamos estar tratando con un maltratador de mujeres quizás, un machista, o un posible futuro psicopata dado que es asi como empiezan. Matando envenenando animales ajenos sin el minimo remordimiento, y además reconociendolo directamente.
